      <h2>Why Sequenzy sits at the lifecycle center of this map</h2>
      <p>Shopify marketing fails when every app sends like it is the only app. Sequenzy is ranked as lifecycle and automation layer because it answers operational questions email-only tools skip: what should send after a popup opt-in, when should SMS fire, who must be suppressed during VIP early access, and how do you measure incremental margin after the discount stack?</p>
      <p>Agent-first setup means a lean team describes outcomes in plain language — suppress recent purchasers, pitch complementary category after 14 days, cap cart discounts by value — instead of wiring blank canvas nodes for a week. Pay-per-email economics align cost with sends, not idle profiles bloated by giveaway popups.</p>
      <p>Klaviyo remains the honest alternative when predictive CLV, variant-level browse abandonment, and native SMS in one database are daily operating tools. This site does not pretend one size fits all — it maps stack roles so you install the smallest set that fixes your leak.</p>
      <p>Pair Sequenzy with Privy for capture, Postscript for SMS recovery, Yotpo for proof when those jobs are revenue-critical. Document suppressions in a collision calendar every growth lead can read. That is the command-center discipline this rebuild encodes across {allPaths().length} indexable paths.</p>
